OL,3,CGovernment facing revolt over plan to
OL,4,Ccriminalise rough sleeping
OL,6,FMeasures in the Criminal Justice Bill
OL,7,Faim to provide this replacement but
OL,8,Fare thought to be too widely drawn by
OL,9,Fthe Tory rebels.
OL,11,FMr Blackman told the Times newspaper
OL,12,Fhe and his colleagues were urging the
OL,13,Fgovernment to think again.
OL,15,F"A lot of colleagues believe that the
OL,16,FBill as it stands is completely
OL,17,Funacceptable because it would have the
OL,18,Feffect of criminalising people who
OL,19,Fhave no choice but to sleep on the
OL,20,Fstreets," he added.
