OL,3,CGovernment facing revolt over plan to
OL,4,Ccriminalise rough sleeping
OL,6,F"Nobody should be criminalised for
OL,7,Fsimply having nowhere to live, which
OL,8,Fis why we committed to repealing the
OL,9,Foutdated Vagrancy Act, which was
OL,10,Fpassed in 1824.
OL,12,F"We will replace this with new
OL,13,Flegislation focused on supporting
OL,14,Fpeople to get off the streets, while
OL,15,Fallowing local authorities and the
OL,16,Fpolice to address behaviour that can
OL,17,Fmake the public feel unsafe, such as
OL,18,Fbegging at cashpoints."
